text: The area of Setana District in Hiyama Subprefecture. is a district located in Hiyama Subprefecture, Hokkaido, Japan. As of 2004, the district has an estimated population of 15,173 and a density of 14.14 persons per km². The total area is 1,072.86 km². ==Towns and villages== *Imakane Category:Districts in Hokkaido
